title: Beethoven - The Very Best of Beethoven (Various, 2005)
description:
The Very Best of Beethoven (2005)


1	Symphony No. 5 in C minor, Op. 67: I. Allegro con brio
	 (Bela Drahos / Nicolaus Esterhazy Sinfonia)
	
2	Egmont, Op. 84: Overture
	 (Stephen Gunzenhauser / Slovak Philharmonic Orchestra)
	
3	Piano Sonata No. 14 in C sharp minor, Op. 27, No. 2, "Moonlight": I. Adagio sostenuto
	 (Jeno Jando)
	
4	String Quartet No. 9 in C major, Op. 59/3, "Razumovsky": IV. Allegro molto
	 (Kodaly Quartet)
	
5	Violin Concerto in D major, Op. 61: III. Rondo: Allegro
	 (Kenneth Jean / Slovak Philharmonic Orchestra / Takako Nishizaki)
	
6	Fidelio, Op. 72, Act I: No. 9 "Abscheulicher! wo eilst du hin?"
	 (Michael Halasz / Nicolaus Esterhazy Sinfonia / Inga Nielsen)
	
7	Piano Sonata No. 8 in C minor, Op. 13, "Pathetique": II. Adagio cantabile
	 (Jeno Jando)
	
8	Symphony No. 6 in F major, Op. 68, "Pastoral": I. Allegro ma non troppo
	 (Bela Drahos / Nicolaus Esterhazy Sinfonia)
	
9	Violin Sonata No. 9 in A major, Op. 47, "Kreutzer": III. Finale: Presto
	 (Takako Nishizaki / Jeno Jando)
	
10	Piano Concerto No. 5 in E flat major, Op. 73, "Emperor": Rondo: Allegro
	 (Barry Wordsworth / Capella Istropolitana / Stefan Vladar)
	
11	Symphony No. 3 in E flat major, Op. 55, "Eroica": III. Scherzo: Allegro vivace
	 (Bela Drahos / Nicolaus Esterhazy Sinfonia)
	
12	Bagatelle in A minor, WoO 59, "Fur Elise"
	 (Balazs Szokolay)
	
13	Mass in D major, Op. 123, "Missa Solemnis": Benedictus
	 (Kenneth Schermerhorn / Nashville Symphony Orchestra & Chorus / Soloists)
	
14	Violin Sonata No. 5 in F major, Op. 24, "Spring": II. Adagio molto espressivo
	 (Takako Nishizaki / Jeno Jando)
	
15	Piano Concerto No. 4 in G major, Op. 58: III. Rondo (Vivace)
	 (Barry Wordsworth / Capella Istropolitana / Stefan Vladar)
	
16	Andante in F major, WoO 57, "Andante favori"
	 (Balazs Szokolay)
	
17	Symphony No. 7 in A major, Op. 92: II. Allegretto
	 (Bela Drahos / Nicolaus Esterhazy Sinfonia)
	
18	Piano Trio No. 7 in B flat major, Op. 97, "Archduke": II. Scherzo
	 (Jeno Jando / Takako Nishizaki / Csaba Onczay)
	
19	Cello Sonata No. 3 in A major, Op. 69: III. Adagio cantabile - Allegro vivace
	 (Maria Kliegel / Nina Tichman)
	
20	Symphony No. 9 in D minor, Op. 125, "Choral": IV. Finale: Presto - Allegro assai (excerpt)
	 (Richard Edlinger / Zagreb Philharmonic Orchestra & Chorus / Soloists)
	



	Composer: Ludwig Van Beethoven (Baptised 1770 - Heaven 1827)



Codec profile is Opus VBR at bitrate 96 (libopus 1.1).
The source was CD/lossless, retail 2005.

Genre marked as Classical, and tracks are tagged and pretty.
Embedded 600x600 custom front cover album art.

Note(s): This is the 2CD "very best of" compilation from the naxos series with the cartoonish abomination album covers. The original album cover is therefore obviously not embedded.
